                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d115">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">811.515/2145: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Costa Rica</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Trueblood</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">San José</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-09-14T17:00:00-06:00"
                            >September 14, 1943—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 11:44 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>646. Reference Department’s telegram 535, August 21, and my despatch No. 545 of
                    September 4. The Minister of Finance has instructed the Junta de Custodia to
                    take the necessary steps to convert the dollar <pb facs="0130" n="116"
                        xml:id="pg_116"/> funds held by the Spanish Minister into colones and block
                    the latter. Foreign Minister Echandi<note n="41" xml:id="d115fn41">Alberto
                        Echandi.</note> has now informed me that this instruction was issued without
                    his consent and has raised the question whether the armistice concluded with the
                    Italian Government may not change the juridical status of these funds and make
                    it inopportune to take action at this time. Since I expect to discuss this
                    matter personally with the Foreign Minister later in the week I shall appreciate
                    receipt of the Department’s views by telegraph.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Trueblood</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
